# Black Box project memory and session handoff

This is the durable handoff for future Codex sessions working on Black Box.
Read it completely before changing the repository. It records where work stopped,
what the user expects, what is already built, the current release state, and the
next safe actions.

Product documentation remains authoritative for implementation details. Never put
passwords, npm tokens, 2FA codes, signing keys, API keys, control tokens, or
captured user evidence in this file.

## Resume protocol

1. Read this file in full.
2. Read docs/complete-project-guide.md for the complete product explanation.
3. Recheck all time-sensitive state before acting:

    git status --short --branch
    git log --oneline --decorate -15
    git rev-list --left-right --count origin/main...main
    git remote -v
    node --version
    npm --version
    npm whoami
    gh repo view --json nameWithOwner,visibility,url,defaultBranchRef
    npm view @blackbox/cli version --json
    npm view @blackbox/protocol version --json

4. Preserve unrelated user changes. Never reset, discard, amend, or squash them
   without explicit permission.
5. Make a local commit for every new feature or important milestone.
6. Do not push to origin, push a tag, create a GitHub release, create an npm token,
   change npm package settings, or publish packages unless the user explicitly
   authorizes that external action in the current session.
7. Publishing guidance is not publication authorization.

