The root npm workspace remains private. The public runtime set is defined by
scripts/runtime-packages.mjs and must currently publish in this order:

1. @blackbox/protocol at packages/protocol
2. @blackbox/storage at packages/storage
3. @blackbox/normalizers at packages/normalizers
4. @blackbox/context at packages/context
5. @blackbox/analysis at packages/analysis
6. @blackbox/daemon at apps/daemon
7. @blackbox/cli at apps/cli

All seven are version 0.1.0, use exact internal 0.1.0 dependencies, declare Node
>=22.15.0, use Apache-2.0, have explicit file allowlists, and set
publishConfig.access to public. The CLI binary is blackbox at ./dist/bin.js.

Dependency graph:

    protocol -> zod
    storage -> protocol, better-sqlite3, zod
    normalizers -> protocol, zod
    context -> protocol
    analysis -> protocol
    daemon -> analysis, context, normalizers, protocol, storage, zod
    cli -> daemon, protocol, storage

These development workspaces must stay private and must not be published:

- Root blackbox workspace
- @blackbox/viewer
- @blackbox/demo-agent
- @blackbox/adapters
- @blackbox/test-fixtures

